  "expected": "reject",
  "expectedErrorCode": "CROSS_TENANT_REFERENCE_FORBIDDEN",
  "expectedGateStep": 10,
  "notes": "The receiver is technically authorized for both tenant_001 AND tenant_002 (in its authorizedTenants set), but that is NOT what authorizes a cross-tenant reference. Cross-tenant references require an explicit, registered crossTenantPolicy (referenced via scope.crossTenantPolicyRef and scopeType=CROSS_TENANT, or — for indirect references — a registered policy authorizing the specific reference subtype across the specific tenant pair). The envelope here uses scopeType=TENANT with tenant_001 but references an artifact in tenant_002 with no policy. Receiver MUST reject. This rule prevents tenant boundary erosion via receiver multi-tenancy."
